<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">

<head>
    <style type="text/css">
        #body \{
            background-color: #2c3339;
            font-family: monospace;
            color: #f5f6f7;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 0 auto;
            font-size: 14px;
        \}

        #logo \{
            margin-top: 10px;
            width: 20%;
            height: auto;
        \}

        h2 \{
            font-weight: normal;
            margin: 40px;
            font-size: 24px;
        \}

        .footer \{
            background-color: #242526;
            padding: 30px;
            margin-top: 40px;
            font-size: 12px;
        \}

        pre \{
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 60%;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 20px auto;
            border: 1px solid;
            border-radius: 2px;
        \}

        .row \{
            font-size: 16px;
            padding-top: 2px;
        \}

        a \{
            color: rgb(174, 129, 255);
        \}
    </style>
</head>

<body id="body">
    <img id="logo"
        src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Exein-io/pulsar/07677de701181ed959a9248841dd6d7285be5003/assets/pulsar-logo-white.png"
        alt="Pulsar logo" />

    <h2>
        Pulsar has identified malicious activity on host <b>{ hostname }</b> at <b>{ timestamp } UTC</b>.
    </h2>

    <div class="row">
        Module <b>{ threat_source }</b> identified the following event from process <b>{ image }</b>:
        <br>
    <pre>{ event_info }</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        This threat event contains this additional piece of information:
        <br>
    <pre>{ threat_info }</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
        <p>For more information about <b>rule-engine</b> generated threat, you can check the documentation <a
                href="https://pulsar.sh/docs/concepts/rules" target="_blank">here</a></p>
        <p>Copyright Â© 2023 Exein, SpA.</p>
    </div>
</body>

</html>
